==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
Proximal pronouns in French (''[[ce]]'', ''[[ici]]'', ''[[ci]]'') and Italian (''[[ci]]'')

===Particle===
# [[here]] (adverbial particle of proximity)
#: ''ĉi'' combines with demonstrative [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlatives]] to indicate that the referrent is somehow near the speaker:
#:* ''[[tiu]] '''ĉi''''': "this [one/person]"
#:* ''[[tio]] '''ĉi''''': "this [thing]"
#:* ''[[tia]] '''ĉi''''': "this kind of"
#:* ''[[ties]] '''ĉi''''': "belonging to these people"
#:* ''[[tiel]] '''ĉi''''': "this [standard] manner or degree"
#:* ''[[tie]] '''ĉi''''': "here"
#:* ''[[tiam]] '''ĉi''''': "then [just past or very soon]"
#:* ''[[tiom]] '''ĉi''''': "this much [of a typical quantity]"
#:* ''[[tial]] '''ĉi''''': "for this [common] reason"

====Antonyms====
* ''[[for]]'': [[distant]] (adverbial particle of distance)

